<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-03-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="146" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d146">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">150.01/802</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Norwegian Minister</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bryn</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-03-19"><hi rend="italic">March 19,
                                1924</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note dated February 20, 1924, with respect to certain
                            provisions of the new immigration bill (H. R. 6540) introduced in the
                            House of Representatives on February 1, 1924.</p>
                        <p>You may be assured that all questions relating to the appropriate
                            recognition of the treaty provisions to which you refer are having
                            proper consideration.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles E.
                            Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>